      <div class="text">
        <p>This Traineeship Opportunity is un-waged Work Experience as part of an entry to work course. </p>

        <p>Work Experience Purpose:</p>

        <p>To gain experience in the provision of effective administrative support to a variety of teams across the Professional Services Area within Centro (Legal, Finance, HR, Procurement), ensuring high levels of standards are delivered through the provision of effective systems, procedures and support services.</p>

        <p>Tasks involved:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Undertake office and systems administration.</li>
          <li>Liaise with relevant internal stakeholders.</li>
          <li>Ensure the proactive co-ordination of diaries and meetings.</li>
          <li>Arrange meeting rooms and refreshments as required.</li>
          <li>Ensure office supplies are monitored and replenished as required.</li>
          <li>Open and distribute post throughout the Directorate.</li>
          <li>Maintain and develop archive and filing systems.</li>
          <li>Maintain electronic database systems.</li>
          <li>Provide general administrative/office support.</li>
          <li>Work flexibly to the needs and requirements of Centro.</li>
          <li>To ensure the security and confidentiality of all files and business matters.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>This traineeship work experience is part of an education and training programme that is focused on giving young people the skills and experience that employers are looking for. At its core is work preparation training, English and maths for those who need it, and a high quality work experience placement. </p>

